[This report is out-of-date -- figures as of 8 Mar 2003 -- & incorrect. As
of Fri 21 Mar 2003, the Ministry of Health of Mauritania has reported a
total of 35 cases (18 laboratory confirmed) of CCHF, including only 6 deaths
(see: Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever - Mauritania (04) 20030324.0732). It
is reproduced here because it contains the additional information that the
most affected regions are Trarza, Brakna, and Hodh Gharbi, to the east of
Nouakchott. -
Mod.CP/JW]
